name: microservices-project
description: This project is a microservices-based application that includes three services: User, Product, and Order. Each service runs on a separate port and communicates with one another to manage user data, product details, and orders. The entire application is containerized using Docker to ensure consistency and ease of deployment.

name: Phonebook-Microservice-Web-Application-with-Python-Flask-MySQL-and-Kubernetes-on-AWS
description: The Phonebook Microservice Web App, using Python Flask and MySQL, is orchestrated with Docker and Kubernetes. It showcases microservice architecture with backend and frontend services managing database interactions. The backend supports CRUD operations, while the frontend enables efficient searching. Persistent volumes maintain database integrity.

name: Monolithic-to-Microservices
description: This project demonstrates converting a monolithic application to microservices. Each arithmetic function (addition, subtraction, multiplication, division, etc.) is an independent service, managed with Docker Compose for efficient deployment and scalability.
